{"id": "1417766646642249819", "channel_id": "1417766646642249819", "type": 0, "author_id": "334271675786854413", "author_name": "darkerkuro", "author_bot": false, "content": "Almost everywhere, not just in the example image, of the Thai UI, the vowels are sink into the letters. \nI’m not sure exactly when it started, but probably since the major UI update, maybe due to a font change or some code adjustment. Since then, there’s been an issue with vowels getting sink in. I understand that Thai uses both vowels and tone marks, so problems like this tend to happen quite often. Still, I hope it will be fixed and improved.\n\nIn the screenshot, I’ve included an example of how it should look.", "timestamp": "2025-09-17T06:58:29.390000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "👍", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "attachments": [{"id": "1417766647728443485", "filename": "44646.png", "content_type": "image/webp", "size": 1674142, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1417766646642249819/1417766647728443485/44646.png?ex=69cc1955&is=69cac7d5&hm=6376d346770890f1f844276aadca629d313d743a644412d626e6f65afe0228c3&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1417766646642249819", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Issue with Thai UI vowel positioning.", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168893200044183"]}
